						               													<description>Olympic Baseball and Softball allows you to replay any of the modern Olympic Baseball and Softball tournaments as you play to see who gets the Gold! Each team is rated for Hit ability and Run percentage. You sum up the Hit For (HF) of the attacking team and Hit Against of the defending team, divide the result by two (rounding down) and convert the result to a letter. Roll two six sided die on the Hits Table and cross the result of the roll with the letter you have found before. The number obtained is the number of hits scored by the attacking team during the game. Now check the conversion percentage of the team to see how many hits become runs: roll a percentage die (two ten sided dice of different colors, one of them for the  tens digits, the other for the single digits) for each hit and if the roll is equal or below the percentage factor, it become a run, otherwise not.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Repeat the procedure for the opposing team and you'll have the final result for the game. In case of a tie, use the Killer Instinct rule.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
